        <article
                class="program-show"
                data-episode-id="818298800" data-episode-date="2020-03-20">

                <div class="program-show__info">
                    <div class="program-show__info-inner">
                        <h2 class="program-show__title">
                            <a href="https://www.npr.org/programs/ted-radio-hour/818298800/irl-online?showDate=2020-03-20"  data-metrics='{"action":"Click Archive View Full Show","category":"Episode Archive","label":"https:\/\/www.npr.org\/programs\/ted-radio-hour\/818298800\/irl-online"}' >IRL Online</a>
                        </h2>

                            <p class="program-show__teaser"><time datetime="2020-03-20"><span class="date">March 20, 2020 &#149; </span></time>Our online lives are now entirely interwoven with our real lives. But the laws that govern real life don't apply online. This hour, TED speakers explore rules to navigate this vast virtual space.</p>

                            <div class="program-show__full-audio">
                                  <b data-play-all='{"type":"episode","full":["818298800:818863126"],"segments":["818299094:818865909","818318821:818867878","818341273:818866140","818358581:818866635","818388307:818867022"],"audioData":[{"uid":"818298800:818863126","available":true,"duration":"3149","title":"IRL Online","audioUrl":"https:\/\/ondemand.npr.org\/anon.npr-mp3\/npr\/ted\/2020\/03\/20200319_ted_ep158_full.mp3?d=3149&story=818298800&t=fullprog&p=&siteplayer=true&size=49137612","storyUrl":"https:\/\/www.npr.org\/programs\/ted-radio-hour\/818298800\/irl-online","slug":"","program":"TED Radio Hour","affiliation":null,"song":"","artist":"","album":"","track":"","type":"segment","subtype":"program"},{"uid":"818299094:818865909","available":true,"duration":417,"title":"Claire Wardle: Why Do We Fall For Misinformation?","audioUrl":"https:\/\/ondemand.npr.org\/anon.npr-mp3\/npr\/ted\/2020\/03\/20200319_ted_ep158_01.mp3?orgId=1&topicId=1019&d=417&p=57&story=818299094&siteplayer=true&size=6672834","storyUrl":"https:\/\/www.npr.org\/2020\/03\/20\/818299094\/claire-wardle-why-do-we-fall-for-misinformation","slug":"Technology","program":"TED Radio Hour","affiliation":"","song":"","artist":"","album":"","track":0,"type":"segment","subtype":"other"},{"uid":"818318821:818867878","available":true,"duration":331,"title":"Zeynep Tufekci: How Do We Build Systems Of Trust Online?","audioUrl":"https:\/\/ondemand.npr.org\/anon.npr-mp3\/npr\/ted\/2020\/03\/20200319_ted_ep158_02.mp3?orgId=1&topicId=1019&d=331&p=57&story=818318821&siteplayer=true&size=5284641","storyUrl":"https:\/\/www.npr.org\/2020\/03\/20\/818318821\/zeynep-tufekci-how-do-we-build-systems-of-trust-online","slug":"Technology","program":"TED Radio Hour","affiliation":"","song":"","artist":"","album":"","track":0,"type":"segment","subtype":"other"},{"uid":"818341273:818866140","available":true,"duration":938,"title":"Edward Snowden: Why Does Online Privacy Matter?","audioUrl":"https:\/\/ondemand.npr.org\/anon.npr-mp