        <article
                class="program-show"
                data-episode-id="813768509" data-episode-date="2020-03-13">

                <div class="program-show__info">
                    <div class="program-show__info-inner">
                        <h2 class="program-show__title">
                            <a href="https://www.npr.org/programs/ted-radio-hour/813768509/reinvention?showDate=2020-03-13"  data-metrics='{"action":"Click Archive View Full Show","category":"Episode Archive","label":"https:\/\/www.npr.org\/programs\/ted-radio-hour\/813768509\/reinvention"}' >Reinvention</a>
                        </h2>

                            <p class="program-show__teaser"><time datetime="2020-03-13"><span class="date">March 13, 2020 &#149; </span></time>Change is hard. Transitions can be tough. But they're also opportunities to discover and reimagine what you thought you knew. In her first episode, Manoush Zomorodi explores the power of reinvention.</p>

